               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-1021" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1021" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1021" type="surname" value="GEDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-1021" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN GEDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I carry on my business in Munster-street, Regent's Park. The prisoner was in my employ to shut up the shop, and has been so about six weeks—I missed several parcels of soap, and accused him of it—he said it was a mistake of mine, he had not stolen it—it passed over—I watched him, and on last Saturday week, I saw something in his pocket.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183602290190"></xptr>
               <p>when he had got about ten yards away—he said he had got nothing—I I said he had got something—he then said it was only a few rags—I told him to pall them out, and I should be satisfied—he would not—I said I would give him in charge, and then he said it was a pound of candles—I said he had robbed me of several pieces of soap—he said, "So help me God, I have taken but one piece"—I then gave him in charge.</p>
